description.narrative: (Bangladesh): USAID's Data for Impact (D4I) activity will provide technical support to local Bangladeshi public and non-governmental organizations to build their capacity to design and conduct rigorous program evaluations, specialized population-based surveys, data analysis, and implementation research using innovative and efficient approaches and tools. With FY 2023 funds, D4I will strengthen the use of data in decision-making at the Bangladesh Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MOHFW) through the provision of a Technical Assistance Support Team to the Program Management and Monitoring Unit of the Planning Wing of MOHFW. Through D4I's technical advisors embedded in the MOHFW, D4I will facilitate the use of evidence to design Bangladesh's next five-year health sector program, expected to begin in 2024. D4I will partner with local organizations to assist with data analysis, research, and developing key policy documents to guide the MOHFW on evidence-based programming. D4I will continue to engage the media to raise awareness on priority health issues and advocate evidence-based health programming. D4I will guide the Directorate General of Family Planning on the nationwide rollout of an electronic management information system using domestic resources. D4I will provide technical assistance to Dhaka University to build the capacity of its junior faculty members and graduate students to develop research capacity. The activity will support the Joint Strategic Plan FY 2022-2026 (USAID and U.S. Department of State) Goal Three, with the U.S. government's Integrated Country Strategy Mission objective of Improving inclusive and equitable health, education, and livelihood services, especially for women, youth, and marginalized groups.

description.narrative: This CA builds awareness on acts of Venezuela's executive and judicial branch towards the National Assembly. Support is provided to civil society organizations (CSOs) that track judicial sector decisions that affect the executive and legislative branches. It also supports CSOs that track freedom of information compliance. This is accomplished through constitutional analyses of the actions taken by the GOV's executive and judicial branches and building awareness internationally and domestically of its findings and conclusions, which are shared widely so that key democratic actors can have verifiable information when informing their constituents regarding decisions by President Maduro and his allies. International pressure as well as pressure by Venezuelan citizens who will now have more information regarding the machinations of the executive and judicial branches could be a determining factor on future attempted machinations by the Supreme Court (TSJ).
